&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engineering Manager | ComparaJá.pt – Lisbon (Hybrid)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly skilled and experienced &lt;strong&gt;Engineering Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to guide our development team in delivering high-quality software. You will own the delivery process end-to-end, ensuring that our products are built to modern development standards while fostering a culture of excellence and velocity. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in software development, experience in coaching and mentoring teams, and a passion for optimising processes to drive efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an office role based in Alvalade, Lisbon with flexibility to work remotely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the delivery of high-quality software:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead the technical direction of projects, ensuring that software is delivered on time, meets business requirements, and adheres to the highest standards of performance, security, and scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimise development processes:&lt;/strong&gt; Continuously review and improve the development lifecycle to increase efficiency, reduce bottlenecks, and enhance productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coach and mentor developers:&lt;/strong&gt; Provide hands-on technical guidance, mentorship, and support to the development team. Foster professional growth and engineering excellence through regular feedback, training, and knowledge sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensure modern development standards:&lt;/strong&gt; Promote and implement best practices, including CI/CD pipelines, automated testing, code reviews, and clean coding principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with product managers, designers, and other stakeholders to align technical decisions with business goals and ensure a shared vision across the product lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Make critical decisions around architecture, tools, and frameworks, ensuring long-term scalability and maintainability of the codebase.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stay updated with industry trends:&lt;/strong&gt; Continuously explore new technologies, frameworks, and methodologies to ensure the team is up-to-date with the latest advancements in software development. Especially concerning the ability to rapidly prototype ideas using AI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
